<HSPACE=3D"12"><FONT color=3D#808080 face=3DTahoma font=3D"">
<P>What began as a conflict over the transfer of consciousness from =
flesh to=20
machines escalated into a war which has decimated a million worlds. The =
Core and=20
the Arm have all but exhausted the resources of a galaxy in their =
struggle for=20
domination. Both sides now crippled beyond repair, the remnants of their =
armies=20
continue to battle in new Galaxies, their hatred fueled by over four =
thousand=20
years of total war. </P>
<P>This is a fight to the death. For each side, the only acceptable =
outcome is=20
the complete elimination of the other.</P>
<P>In the far future the galaxy is ruled by a benevolent central body of =
humans=20
and artificial intelligences called the Core (a contraction of =
"Consciousness=20
Repository". The Core's technological and economic triumphs have allowed =

humanity to colonize most of the Milky Way and enjoy peace and =
prosperity. </P>
<P>However, the balance is broken by a technological breakthrough which =
allows=20
the consciousness of a human being to be reliably transferred into a =
machine,=20
thereby granting theoretically indefinite life in a process called =
"patterning".=20
</P>
<P>The Core have one conciousness, but several sub-routines to handle =
mundane=20
affairs. Therefore communication is through a proxy program. No known =
image of=20
the Conciousness exists.</P>
<P>Though once human, The Core now dispise all non-patterned entities. =
Their=20
hated rivals, the Arm, will be eliminated on sight. Recently gated into =
a new=20
Galaxy, The Core will quickly try and dominate all.</P>
<P>The Core are from my favorite RTS Total Annihilation. </P>
<P>Their prefered weapons are Railguns, Bombardment, Area, and=20
Ion.</P></FONT></DIV></BODY></HTML>

